title: For Sale:  1964 Winchester 70,  243 Caliber
postcontent: This is not a Pre-1964 Winchester, instead this is the first year of the next generation 1964 Winchester 70, in a light caliber (.243). Low recoil, perhaps for those not seeking full recoil, or lighter individuals. This caliber is fully capable as a deer rifle or varmint rifle.This beautifully crafted walnut stock rivals today’s the higher priced ‘Super Grade’ quality. Barrel length is estimated at 22” and in flawless quality. Obviously lightly used. Optional equipment includes the new Leupold VX-2 (3-9X, 40mm), value $300, and can be removed for $250 reduced selling price, if no scope is required. Approx 30 rounds of Winchester .243 ammo included (100 Grain). Hoyt leather trimmed canvas rifle bag, valued at $60 is included.This Rifleman’s rifle needs little introduction, introduced first in the 1930’s, it has been the standard by which all bolt action rifles are judged. The 1964-1992 Winchester Model 70 differed from the pre-1964 models by forging the receiver for the first time, which increased strength and reduced machining  labor. The bolt action was also changed, with the bolt face now fully surrounding the cartridge rim. Although cheaper to manufacture than the prior undercut bolt face, and built as 2 separate pieces then brazed together, it is considered stronger.
